reviewText: I was hesitant about purchasing this concert but my wife and I love Brian Stokes Mitchell and figured even if we only liked his numbers, it would still be worth the price.  However, in addition to enjoying Mitchell's songs, we were pleasantly surprised to discover that the rest of the concert was equally as good. Brilliant spectacle, fantastic sound, top-notch quality, a joyous celebration of Christmas throughout!  Unexpectedly, this turned out to be the Christmas DVD we shared with all of our guests throughout the Christmas season.  Also:  excellent documentary features.  Highly recommended.

reviewText: The combination of the performing talents of Brian Stokes Mitchell and the Mormon Tabernacle Choir and Orchestra at Temple Square is simply superb. The arrangements by Mack Wilberg make well-known Christmas standards fresh and exciting. Mr. Mitchell's enthusiasm and passion for the material are a joy to experience.
summary: A wonderful addition to any Christmas music collection
